text: Kennedia lateritia (Augusta Kennedia) is a species of flowering plant in the family Fabaceae, endemic to the south-west of Western Australia. The species was formally described in 1864 by von Mueller in Fragmenta Phytographiae Australiae 4. It is a declared threatened species ==References== ==External links== *Australasian Virtual Herbarium (AVH): Occurrence data for Kennedia lateritia'.
